{"lemma": "عارِضٌ", "slug": "عارِضٌ", "root": "ع.ر.ض", "root_slug": "ع-ر-ض", "root_link": "/words/roots/ع-ر-ض", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "عارِض", "root": "عرض", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 2}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 2, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 11}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["", "n28712"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%90%D8%B6%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "cloud", "fa": "ابر", "ur": "بادل", "tr": "bulut", "id": "awan", "bn": "মেঘ", "es": "nube", "fr": "nuage", "de": "Wolke", "ru": "облако", "zh": "云"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "exhibitor"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "demonstrator"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "obstacle"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "accident (something that happens by chance)"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "anomalous situation"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "calamity"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "attack (e.g. of nerves, of an illness)"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "cheek, side of the face"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "molar tooth"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "something that intercepts the vision (mountain, cloud, etc.)"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "present, gift"}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Derived from the active participle of عَرَضَ (ʕaraḍa, “to happen, to exhibit”)."}, "ipa": ["/ʕaː.ridˤ/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n28712", "headword_ar": "عَارِضٌ", "root": "ErD", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Showing its breadth,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "width;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaraDa", "text_ar": "عَرَضَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", first signification;) or]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "having its side apparent:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) and [in like manner] ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muEoriDN", "text_ar": "مُعْرِضٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", q. v., anything"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "showing its breadth,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "width:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "its side:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] (TA:) [and hence, both signify"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "appearing."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(See again"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaraDa", "text_ar": "عَرَضَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".)] ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A collection of clouds appearing,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "presenting itself,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "extending sideways,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muEotariDN", "text_ar": "مُعْتَرِضٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the horizon;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O, K;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "overpeering:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a collection of clouds which one sees in a side of the sky, like that which is termed"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "julobN", "text_ar": "جُلْبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "except that the former is white, whereas the latter inclines to blackness, and is narrower than the former, and more distant:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(AZ:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a collection of clouds that comes over against one"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muEaAriDFA", "text_ar": "مُعَارِضًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the sky, unexpectedly:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(El-Báhilee, O:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a collection of clouds that appears,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "presents itself,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "extends sideways,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaEotariDu", "text_ar": "يَعْتَرِضُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the sky, like as does a mountain, before it covers the sky,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saHaAbN EaAriDN", "text_ar": "سَحَابٌ عَارِضٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HabiY~N", "text_ar": "حَبِىٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (As, O:) pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EawaAriDu", "text_ar": "عَوَارِضُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) [See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaroDN", "text_ar": "عَرْضٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EiroDN", "text_ar": "عِرْضٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] In the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAriDN", "text_ar": "عَارِضٌ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mumoTirunaA", "text_ar": "مُمْطِرُنَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in the Kur [xlvi. 23],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mmTrnA", "text_ar": "ممطرنا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "means"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mumoTirN", "text_ar": "مُمْطِرٌ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lanaA", "text_ar": "لَنَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; for as being determinate it cannot be an epithet to"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAriDN", "text_ar": "عَارِضٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which is indeterminate: and the like of this the Arabs do only in the instances of nouns derived from verbs; so that you may not say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h`*aA rajulN gulaAmunaA", "text_ar": "هٰذَا رَجُلٌ غُلَامُنَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S, O.) ―         -b3-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaroDN", "text_ar": "عَرْضٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in the sentence commencing with “ A mountain, ” in two places: ―         -b4-  and again, shortly after. ―         -b5-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A gift appearing"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(As, S, O, K) from a person. (As, S, O.) [See an ex. voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAy^iDN", "text_ar": "عَايِضٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] ―         -b6-  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Happening; befalling; occurring: an occurrence;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as a fever, and the like. (See"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaraDa lahu", "text_ar": "عَرَضَ لَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".)]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A bane,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "cause of mischief, that occurs in a thing;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaraDN", "text_ar": "عَرَضٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", q. v. (TA.) And ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$ubohapN EaAriDapN", "text_ar": "شُبْهَةٌ عَارِضَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A doubt,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "dubiousness, occurring,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "intervening, in the mind."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) In the saying of 'Alee,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaqodaHu Al$~ak~u fiY", "text_ar": "يَقْدَحُ الشَّكُّ فِى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mino $ubohapK", "text_ar": "مِنْ شُبْهَةٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qalobihi biA^aw~ali EaAriDapK", "text_ar": "قَلْبِهِ بِاَوَّلِ عَارِضَةٍ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", the word"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EArDp", "text_ar": "عارضة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "may perhaps be an inf. n., [or a quasi-inf. n.,] like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAqibapN", "text_ar": "عَاقِبَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAfiyapN", "text_ar": "عَافِيَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (TA:) [so that the meaning may be"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Doubt makes an impression upon his heart at the first occurrence of dubiousness."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] ―         -b7-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Whatever faces one,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a thing: (TA, and so in some copies of the K: in other copies of the K, this signification is given to ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAriDapN", "text_ar": "عَارِضَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "anything facing one."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O.) ―         -b8-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Intervening; preventing: an intervening,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a preventing, thing; an obstacle:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a thing that prevents one's going on; such as a mountain and the like."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb.) [Its application to a cloud, and some other applications to which reference has been made above, may be derived from this signification, or from that next preceding, or from the first.] ―         -b9-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EuroDN", "text_ar": "عُرْضٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in the first of the senses assigned to this latter above; as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAriDapN", "text_ar": "عَارِضَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (The former accord. to some copies of the K: the latter accord. to others: but both accord. to the TA.) ―         -b10-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "What appears,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of the face, (K,) or of the mouth, accord. to the L, (TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "when one laughs."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L, K, TA: but in some copies of the K, and in the O, this signification is given to ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAriDapN", "text_ar": "عَارِضَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) ―         -b11-  The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "side of the cheek"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA) of a man; (TA;) as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAriDapN", "text_ar": "عَارِضَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (O, L, K;) the two sides of the two cheeks of a man being called the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAriDaAni", "text_ar": "عَارِضَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Msb, TA,) or the ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAriDataAni", "text_ar": "عَارِضَتَانِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S:) the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "two sides of the face:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lh, O, K:) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "side of the face;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaruwDN", "text_ar": "عَرُوضٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; the two together being called the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAriDaAni", "text_ar": "عَارِضَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Lh, TA:) or this last signifies the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "two sides of the mouth:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "two sides of the beard:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EawaAriDu", "text_ar": "عَوَارِضُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xafiyfu AlEaAriDayoni", "text_ar": "خَفِيفُ العَارِضَيْنِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Light,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "scanty, in the hair of the two sides of the cheeks,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O, Msb,) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the beard;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O;) being elliptical. (Msb.) But in a certain trad., in which a happy quality of a man is said to be"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xif~apu EaAriDayohi", "text_ar": "خِفَّةُ عَارِضَيْهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", the meaning is said to be (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "His activity in praising and glorifying God;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "his not ceasing to move the sides of his cheeks by praising and glorifying God."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IAth, on the authority of El-Khattábee; and O.) ―         -b12-  The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "side of the neck;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K;) the two sides thereof being called the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAriDaAni", "text_ar": "عَارِضَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (IDrd, O:) pl. as above. (TA.) [See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EuroDN", "text_ar": "عُرْضٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", near the beginning.] ―         -b13-  The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "tooth that is in the side of the mouth:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA; and K, as in some copies of the latter; but in other copies, this signification is given to ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAriDapN", "text_ar": "عَارِضَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":) pl. as above: (K:) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "side of the mouth;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S;) and so, as some say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EawaAriDu", "text_ar": "عَوَارِضُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (TA;) [meaning the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "teeth in the side of the mouth;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for] you say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AimoraA^apN naqiy~apu AlEaAriDi", "text_ar": "اِمْرَاَةٌ نَقِيَّةُ العَارِضِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlEawaAriDi", "text_ar": "العَوَارِضِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a woman clean in the side of the mouth:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, TA:) and Jereer describes a woman as polishing her"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAriDaAni", "text_ar": "عَارِضَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "with a branch of a beshámeh, [a tree of which the twigs are used for cleaning the teeth,] meaning, as Aboo-Nasr says, the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "teeth that are after the central incisors,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "which latter are not of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EwArD", "text_ar": "عوارض"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": or, accord. to ISk,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAriDN", "text_ar": "عَارِضٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "canine tooth and"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Diros", "text_ar": "ضِرْس"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bicuspid"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "next thereto:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or, as some say,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "what are between the central incisor and the"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "first"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Drs", "text_ar": "ضرس"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[which is a"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bicuspid"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (S, O:) some say that the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EwArD", "text_ar": "عوارض"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "are the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "central incisors,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as being [each] in the side of the mouth: others, that they are the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "teeth next to the sides of the mouth:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "others, that they are"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "four teeth next to the canine teeth, and followed by the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aDoraAs", "text_ar": "اَضْرَاس"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": Lh says that they are"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ADrAs", "text_ar": "اضراس"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": others, that they are the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "teeth that are between the central incisors and the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ADrAs", "text_ar": "اضراس"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": and others, that they are"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "eight teeth in each side; four above, and four below."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA [from the O &c.].)       -A2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAriDN", "text_ar": "عَارِضٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as applied to a she-camel, or a sheep or goat: see the paragraph next following.       -A3-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Giving"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "a thing, or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "giver"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a thing,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in exchange,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for ("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mino", "text_ar": "مِنْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ") another thing. (TA.) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A reviewer of an army,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of a body of soldiers, who makes them to pass by him, and examines their state."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S.)       -A4-  See also the next paragraph; last three sentences."}], "source_refs": ["TA", "AZ", "As", "O", "S", "K", "Msb", "Lh", "IDrd"]}]}, "classical_definitions": {"source": "hawramani", "url": "https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%B6/", "headword_ar": "عارض", "entries": [{"lexicon_id": "dictionary_18", "lexicon_en": "Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)", "lexicon_ar": "كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني", "permalink": "https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23398#840f90", "body_html": "<span>العارض للشيء: ما يكون محمولًا عليه خارجًا عنه، والعارض أعم من العرض؛ إذ يقال للجوهر عارض كالصورة تعرض على الهيولى، ولا يقال له: عرض.</span>"}]}, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}